import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data.boxplot(column='total', by='region')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of total income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['income_per_capita'] = data['total'] * data['pct']
    avg_income = data.groupby('region')['income_per_capita'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(avg_income.index, avg_income.values)
    ax.set_title('What is the average income per capita in each region?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Income per Capita')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['region', 'group']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.pivot(index='region', columns='group', values='counts')
    data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income groups across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Income Group')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
